Tanzanian star Darassa is the star of the moment.His hit single Muziki is basically the soundtrack of every urban youth's life. When they are not singing along to the jam, they are to quoting his punchlines like"Sio simba, sio chui, sio mamba." The reigning king of music, was supposed to be in town this weekend.The Too Much hitmakerr was set to headline last weekend&rsquo;s event at Xs Millionaires. But we found out that the star and his manager called off the event because of &ldquo;miscommunication&rdquo;.Darassa&rsquo;s manager, Hanscana, told Word Is in a phone interview that the miscommunication emanated from conversion of currency from Tanzanian shillings to dollars.&ldquo;Our fee was 5 million Tanzanian shillings, but they must have gotten the currency conversion wrong because they sent us USD 1000 which falls short of the full fee. When we checked in our accounts before we came we did not get the full fee as earlier agreed, thus the event had to be canceled,&rdquo; Hanscana said.For the Darassa fans, don&rsquo;t lose hope, the manager promised that they are &ldquo;still talking&rdquo;.Listen to the audio to get the full plans for the next show;&lt;iframe width="100%" height="450" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/307061115&amp;amp;auto_play=false&amp;amp;hide_related=false&amp;amp;show_comments=true&amp;amp;show_user=true&amp;amp;show_reposts=false&amp;amp;visual=true"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;